> If you were in Italy, you might come across this dish under its traditional name,
> Orecchiette ai Broccoletti. It's a classic Italian dish composed of a few simple
> ingredients, making for a quick and delicious weeknight dinner!

Prep: Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of @water{} and @salt{} to a boil.
Trim and discard the bottom inch from the @baby broccolini{12%ounce}, then cut into
1-inch pieces. Remove the @sweet Italian pork sausage{18%ounce} from the casings.

Boil the pasta: Add the @orecchiette pasta{12%ounce} to the boiling water and cook
for ~{9-11%minutes}, until al dente. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.

Cook the broccolini: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #pan over medium
heat. Add the broccolini and cook, tossing for ~{5-7%minutes}, until tender.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

Cook the sausage: Heat another drizzle of @olive oil{} in the same pan over
medium-high heat. Add the sausage and cook, breaking up the meat into pieces for
~{4-5%minutes}, until browned and cooked through. Add a pinch of @chili flakes{1%tsp}
to the pan (if desired) and cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Toss and serve: Add the pasta, broccolini, @parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}, pasta water,
and 1/4 cup @pesto{4%ounce} to the pan and toss to combine. Cook, tossing for
~{1-2%minutes}, until a sauce has formed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Enjoy!